Bank of Japan Adds $63 Billion to Financial System to Help Boost Liquidity

-- B y   S a b u r o   F u n a b i k i
-- 
2011-03-17T00:15:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/bank-of-japan-adds-63-billion-to-financial-system-to-help-boost-liquidity.html
The Bank of Japan added 5 trillion
yen ($63 billion) to the financial system in a one-day operation
today to help ease liquidity.  The move brings the total size of emergency one-day
operations this week to 33 trillion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saburo Funabiki in  Tokyo  at 
 sfunabiki@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rocky Swift at   rswift5@bloomberg.net . 